Compilation: 
To compile the executable, please use the command "make" or "make all".
This executable will be named "myInterpreter" (myInterpreter.exe on windows)

Usage :
This executable needs another executable, compiled on the specific minix format.
To use it, do the command "./myInterpreter file", with "file" being the name of the executable to interpret
You can add the tag "-m" (ex: "./myInterpreter -m file") to detail every instruction or change of value in the simulated cpu and memory

Architecture : 
This interpreter works on the disassembler, it will give the code to the disassembler, and interpret the string instruction, making it easier to understand. 
The CPU files are there to create the virtual CPU and memory, it also contains most of the functions that only act on it.
All code is commented.

Comments/Overall impressions:
Interesting course with a lot of pratical work.
